    <h1>1. Web Development:</h1>
        <ul>
            <li>Web development is one of the most popular and useful skills in today’s digital world. It involves creating and
            maintaining websites and web applications that people use every day, such as social media platforms, online shopping
            sites, and educational portals. Web development is mainly divided into three parts: front-end, back-end, and full-stack
            development. Front-end development focuses on the design and layout of a website using technologies like HTML, CSS, and
            JavaScript, making the site attractive and user-friendly. Back-end development deals with the server, databases, and
            application logic using languages such as Python, Java, or PHP. Full-stack developers handle both front-end and back-end
            tasks. Learning web development helps students build creative projects, improve problem-solving skills, and opens up
            many career opportunities like web designer, developer, or freelancer. It is a valuable course for anyone interested in
            technology and innovation.</li>
        </ul>
    <h1>2. Communication Skills:</h1>
        <ul>
            <li>Effective communication is a vital skill in both personal and professional life. Our communication skills course focuses on
            enhancing students' ability to express ideas clearly, listen actively, and interact confidently with others. The course covers
            various aspects of communication, including verbal and non-verbal communication, public speaking, and interpersonal skills.
            Students will have opportunities to practice these skills through role-playing exercises, group discussions, and presentations.
            By the end of the course, students will be better equipped to communicate effectively in different situations and contexts.</li>
        </ul>
    <h1>3. App Development:</h1>
        <ul>
            <li>App development is the process of creating software applications that run on mobile devices, tablets, or computers. It
            mainly focuses on building apps for platforms like Android and iOS, which people use daily for communication,
            entertainment, learning, and business. App development is divided into front-end (user interface) and back-end (data
            handling and server logic). Developers use languages like Java, Kotlin, or Swift for mobile apps, and tools like Flutter
            or React Native to build apps that work on multiple platforms. App development requires creativity, logical thinking,
            and problem-solving skills to design smooth and user-friendly experiences. Learning app development can help students
            create their own apps, start startups, or work as professional developers, making it a highly valuable and in-demand
            skill in today’s technology-driven world.</li>
        </ul>
    <h1>4. UPSC / TNPSC Coaching:</h1>
        <ul>UPSC and TNPSC coaching is designed to prepare students for competitive government exams conducted by the Union Public
        Service Commission and the Tamil Nadu Public Service Commission. These exams are highly respected and provide
        opportunities to work in prestigious government positions such as IAS, IPS, and various state administrative roles.
        Coaching programs help students understand the exam pattern, syllabus, and important topics like history, geography,
        polity, economics, and current affairs. They also provide regular tests, study materials, and guidance from experienced
        teachers to improve performance.
        
        UPSC coaching mainly focuses on national-level exams, which are more competitive and require deep understanding and
        strong analytical skills. TNPSC coaching, on the other hand, is focused on Tamil Nadu state-level exams and includes
        topics related to Tamil language, culture, and state-specific knowledge. These coaching classes help students build
        discipline, improve time management, and develop confidence to succeed in exams. It is a great option for students who
        aim to serve the public and build a stable and respected career in government service.</ul>
